<br>
I had the best time last week I have ever had in EQ and wanted to share it with my fellow mages. I and a friend of mine (60 druid) cleared the north wing in HS alone. We really needed to use or wits and be extremely careful crawling thru the dungeon. I was real nervous because as you know HS isn't a great place to do a cr.<br>
<br>
For those complaining about pets, my advise is get your epic. I wasn't in an uber guild when I got mine but I did ask a big guild if I could join them in sky. i was there for 3 days and was rewarded with a crown.<br>
<br>
I have dueled 60 level warriors and my pets eat them up due to thier damage shield. So we have a pet that can outtank a 60 warrior, which we can heal and we can still nuke from behind him. We are a powerful class and I am happier than hell to be a mage.<br>
<br>
My main concern is if our fellow mages keep bitching about everything about a mage, you bring attention to use and I feel the next step is a nerf to us. Who cares that our coth doesnt work in certain zones.Do you actually go to those zones to get exp. or is it a guild raid?<br>
<br>
The excuse of I will never get a group if I don't have coth is just ridiculous. If people are just grouping you for coth, maybe thats the wrong group. All other classes have problems finding a group as well. It's not just specific to mages. Find people who you have grouped with that play at the same time as you and make your own group. Get thier e-mail and send info on where and when to meet.Take the inititive people instead of just crying.<br>
<br>
You either piss with the pups or bark with the dogs.....<br>
<br>
This Gnome barks and bites.<br>
<br>
Thanks for your time,<br>
<br>
Master Thothamen<br>
